The paper deals with graph reassembling, which is a problem in network analysis and can be seen as a form of graph partitioning. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The paper also discusses the optimization of the reassembling process, which involves minimizing certain measures, indicating a possible connection to the Game Theory (cs.GT) or Combinatorics (cs.CC) categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of polynomial-time reductions to show NP-hardness, which is a common technique in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
